# Strava Fitness EDA Project

This project performs exploratory data analysis on Strava fitness activity data to understand workout patterns, performance trends, and training consistency. 
The analysis covers activities such as running, cycling, and walking using metrics like distance, duration, pace, speed, elevation gain, calories burned, and activity frequency.
The project includes data cleaning, transformation, statistical analysis, and visualization to identify weekly and monthly trends, preferred activity types, personal performance changes, and overall fitness progress.

## Key Objectives

* Analyze total activities, distance, and workout duration
* Compare running, cycling, and walking performance
* Study pace, speed, calories, and elevation trends
* Identify workout consistency and activity frequency
* Detect performance improvements and personal patterns
* Create meaningful charts and visual insights

## Tools Used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Jupyter Notebook

## Outcome

The analysis provides a clear overview of fitness habits and performance, helping users understand their training behavior, monitor progress, and make informed decisions to improve consistency and overall fitness.
